info.title: List App
info.description: List definition CRUD operations and memberships discovery and management

put.summary: Adds records with ids provided to the list

requestBody.description: List of recordIds to add to the list

put.summary: Adds to target list all the members from source list
put.description: Add to list all the members of source list

put.summary: Restore the recently deleted list. Only lists deleted within 90 days can be restored

delete.summary: Deletes the list definition with possibility to restore it for up to 90 days after deletion

get.summary: Returns ids of records that are members of the list ordered by recordId

parameters.name: after
parameters.description: The paging cursor token of the last successfully read resources. Calls that only contain partial memberships for the list will contain *paging.prev* and/or *paging.next* data which includes ***before***/***after*** offsets where applicable. Record IDs are ordered in ascending order. This parameter will take precedence over ***before*** if both are provided

parameters.name: before
parameters.description: The paging cursor token for records that come before last successfully read resources . Calls that only contain partial memberships for the list will contain *paging.prev* and/or *paging.next* data which includes ***before***/***after*** offsets where applicable. Record IDs are ordered in descending order.This parameter will be ignored if both ***before*** and ***after*** are used together within the same request.

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: This parameter lets you specify the max number of records returned within API response. Default value (if it isnâ€™t specified) is 100 records. Maximum records count that can be returned is 250.

put.summary: Removes records with ids provided from the list
